Yes. ✅
You must add a .gitignore file — especially since you are using:

.venv/

__pycache__/

Streamlit

PyCharm

Without .gitignore, you risk pushing:

Your virtual environment (very heavy ❌)

Compiled Python files

IDE settings

System junk files

That looks unprofessional.

✅ Create .gitignore in Project Root

Create this file:

resume-skill-gap-analyzer/.gitignore

Put this inside:

# ===============================
# Python
# ===============================
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# Virtual Environment
.venv/
venv/
env/

# Streamlit secrets
.streamlit/secrets.toml

# PyCharm / IntelliJ
.idea/

# VS Code
.vscode/

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs
*.log